bilingual.source: I go to the Book Club and the Volleyball Club.
bilingual.target: 我参加读书俱乐部和排球俱乐部。

bilingual.source: The running club is more popular than the swimming club.
bilingual.target: 跑步俱乐部比游泳俱乐部更受欢迎。
我可以加入你的俱乐部吗？

bilingual.source: He is a member of the club.

list.abstract: 俱乐部（又称会所），单从字面上理解就是人们聚集在一起进行娱乐活动的组织团体或者其场所，严格解释是具有某种相同兴趣的人进行社会交际、文化娱乐等活动的团体和场所。俱乐部是一个外来词，来源于club一词的英语发音[klʌb]。

yingyinNormal.en: Except that it was really the I Hate Rachel Club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但它真的是“我恨瑞秋俱乐部”。

yingyinNormal.en: And what was the name of the club? Cafe. Hey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有，那家俱乐部叫什么？嗨。咖啡馆。

yingyinNormal.en: We're the non-judging breakfast club. We're your best friends.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们是"非指责早餐俱乐部"成员，我们是你最好的朋友。

yingyinNormal.en: The Secret Club
yingyinNormal.zh: 秘密俱乐部

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. Can I be in your secret club, please? Please, I've always wanted to be in a secret club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，我能进你们的秘密俱乐部吗。拜托了，我一直很想加入这种秘密俱乐部。

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose it doesn't have to be a secret secret club. It can be everybody's secret club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是我想秘密俱乐部也不是非得有秘密你们说对不对。他可以是每个人都可以加入的俱乐部。

yingyinNormal.en: Obviously I didn't handle it very well. But if you think about it the I Hate Rachel Club was really the I Love Rachel Club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我处理的不好，如果你把“我恨瑞秋俱乐部”想成“我爱瑞秋俱乐部”。

yingyinNormal.en: Farkle's gone. He gave up the chess club. He gave up the chemistry club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 法尔科已死，他退出了象棋社，退出了化学俱乐部。

yingyinNormal.en: I've always wanted to be in a secret club. We can't have everyone in the secret club. It wouldn't be a secret. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我一直都很想加入秘密俱乐部呢。我们的俱乐部里不能把所有人都加进来。那样的话就不是什么秘密了。哦。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm thinking of joining an "I Hate Turkey Club." Although, I do love a turkey club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我考虑要加入“我恨火鸡俱乐部”，虽然我喜欢吃火鸡三明治。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm not saying that! I'm saying why don't you take scrutting pennies so I can… what you've made and start the club! Start a club that no one wants to go?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不是这个意思，我是说为什么你不带着一点点地攒着小钱...你的成果然后开俱乐部呢？开一个人人都不去的俱乐部吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Wow. Can I be in your secret club? It's not easy to get into. You have to say the secret word.
yingyinNormal.zh: 喔，我也可以加入你的俱乐部吗。嘘，想要加入俱乐部可不容易。你必须说出那个暗号才可以加入。

yingyinNormal.en: I didn't realize I was in an all-male club until that minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我直到这时才意识到自己来到了一家全男性俱乐部。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe I should open a divorced men's club. Dude that is so sad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 或许我该成立一个离婚男子俱乐部。兄弟，那太惨了。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna move my club house there, and park it right next to the falls.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要把俱乐部搬到那里，把它安置在瀑布的旁边。

yingyinNormal.en: You talk to my Daddy. But don't say anything about our secret club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你去和我爸爸说话。但是关于秘密俱乐部什么都不要提。

yingyinNormal.en: You said yourself no one wants to go to that club. No one wants to go to a club called "Chicken on a Stick". So change the name!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你自己说过没人想去那里。没人想去什么鸡肉串俱乐部。那换个名字啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, there you're, Mummy Sheep. What's new? Secret club. Oh, no. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有人吗，啊，你在这啊，羊妈妈。额，秘密俱乐部。哦不。哦。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, divorced men are not bad men. They have that on the napkins at the club.
yingyinNormal.zh: 离婚男人不是坏男人。他们把那句话印在俱乐部的纸巾上。

yingyinNormal.en: Are we going to some secret club to see the best unsigned band in Brooklyn?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们是要去一家秘密俱乐部，看布鲁克林最好的地下乐队演出吗？
